import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from math import pi, asin
theta = np.linspace(0, 4.*pi, 100)
fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize = (5, 5))
for rho in [0., 0.4, 0.8, 0.9, 1.]:
phase = asin(rho)
ax.plot(np.cos(theta), np.sin(theta + phase), label = "$\\
rho = %.1f$" % rho)
